OL,3,CUK-wide E.coli outbreak: What do we
OL,4,Cknow so far?
OL,6,FIf people have been infected with
OL,7,FE.coli they will usually be aware
OL,8,Fwithin three to four days, but
OL,9,Fsymptoms can appear as late as two
OL,10,Fweeks after.
OL,12,FWhere is E.Coli found and how is it
OL,13,Fspread?
OL,15,FFound in the gut and faeces of many
OL,16,Fanimals, particularly cattle, it can
OL,17,Fbe caught by eating contaminated food,
OL,18,Fraw leafy vegetables or undercooked
OL,19,Fmeat.
