OL,3,CUK-wide E.coli outbreak: What do we
OL,4,Cknow so far?
OL,6,FOther symptoms include stomach cramps
OL,7,Fand fever. Symptoms can last up to two
OL,8,Fweeks in uncomplicated cases.
OL,10,FSome patients, mainly children, may
OL,11,Fdevelop haemolytic uraemic syndrome
OL,12,F(HUS) which is a serious life-
OL,13,Fthreatening condition resulting in
OL,14,Fkidney failure.
OL,16,FA small proportion of adults may
OL,17,Fdevelop a similar condition called
OL,18,Fthrombotic thrombocytopaenic purpura
OL,19,F(TTP).
